        "content": "<p>I'm enjoying the ability to perform (nested) pattern matching as in <code>rcases i with ⟨i, ⟨⟩⟩</code>. I would love to be able to use induction more neatly in a similar way, such as <code>induction x with _ | ⟨x, ih⟩</code> - is this possible?</p>\n<p>So far the ways I know to perform induction (let's say on a Nat), look like the following:</p>\n<p>using <code>expose_names</code>, which feels awkward.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- zero case stuff</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expose_names</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- not ideal</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">-- succ case stuff</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>using explicit constructor names, with the ability to name new variables:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- zero case stuff</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">succ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ih</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- succ case stuff</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>using <code>next</code>, with the ability to name new variables:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">next</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- zero case stuff</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">next</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ih</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- succ case stuff</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>What I would love:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨⟩|⟨</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ih</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- zero case stuff</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- succ case stuff</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is this already doable somehow, and are there any other forms I'm missing? I know this is kinda nitpicking, as I can achieve everything I need with the existing notations. I suppose this doesnt have to be a question about <code>induction</code> at all, but other ways of giving names to new variables in various goals.</p>",
        "id": 568104466,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Buckley",
        "timestamp": 1768436840
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"115259\">Scott Buckley</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/.60induction.60.20naming.20newly.20instantiated.20variables.20like.20.60rcases/near/568104466\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>other ways of giving names to new variables in various goals</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>You can also use <code>rename_i</code> which is a fine-grained <code>expose_names</code>.</p>",
